        -:  304:/// The format specification is provided in the range [fmtBegin, fmtEnd).  For
        -:  305:/// truncating conversions, ntrunc is set to the desired maximum number of
        -:  306:/// characters, for example "%.7s" calls formatValue with ntrunc = 7.
        -:  307:///
        -:  308:/// By default, formatValue() uses the usual stream insertion operator
        -:  309:/// operator<< to format the type T, with special cases for the %c and %p
        -:  310:/// conversions.
